==English==
=== Etymology ===
From the Latin ''[[quadra-]]'' + ''[[plegic]]'' from the Greek ''[[plessein]]'' "to strike"; probably patterned after [[paraplegic]] from the Greek ''[[paraplegie]]'' "the paralysis of half of the body"

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːdʒɪk|-iːdʒɪk]]

=== Noun ===
'''quadriplegic'''
# one who suffers from [[quadriplegia]]

